page.title: 01S. ISLANDS - EDRACHILLES BAY
page.content: This area is nearly entirely composed of sea. There is only a small bit of mainland in the east and a few small uninhabited islands. On the mainland there is part of the Duartbeg Nature Reserve which is composed of deciduous trees. It is one of the few areas od deciduous woodland in North West Scotland. There is a small road leading to the reserve, at the end of which is a derelict farmhouse. On the coastline there is a large amount of seaweed which grows well in the relatively warm Atlantic Ocean.
